# Portfolio Project Context

This is Stav Lobel's personal portfolio website built with React, TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS.

## Project Overview
- Single-page application showcasing projects, skills, and contact information
- Automatic GitHub repository fetching and display
- LinkedIn profile picture integration
- Dark mode as default with toggle support
- Responsive design with modern UI components
- Custom green (Slytherin) theme with professional styling

## Key Features
- **GitHub API Integration**: Automatically fetches and displays repositories
- **Technology Detection**: Smart detection of tech stack from repository languages
- **Profile Picture**: LinkedIn integration with fallback to initials
- **Contact Section**: Email, LinkedIn, and GitHub links
- **Project Sorting**: By creation date with featured project highlighting
- **Performance Optimized**: Code splitting, lazy loading, minified bundles

## Technology Stack
- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Vite
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS, shadcn-ui components
- **APIs**: GitHub REST API, LinkedIn profile integration
- **Deployment**: GitHub Actions + Hostinger FTP
- **Quality**: ESLint, TypeScript strict mode, conventional commits

## Development Guidelines
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow TypeScript strict typing
- Implement responsive design patterns
- Maintain clean component architecture
- Use semantic HTML and accessibility best practices
- Keep bundle size optimized


This context should inform all code generation and assistance to align with the project's professional, polished, and technical nature.
